OL,3,COne in 1,000 people could have gene
OL,4,Cputting them at risk of rare heart
OL,5,Ccondition
OL,7,FThe result was much higher among
OL,8,Fpatients with African ancestry with
OL,9,Fabout one in 23, or 4.3%, having genes
OL,10,Flinked to the disease.
OL,12,FThose with the variant ` known as
OL,13,FVal142Ile ` were more likely to have
OL,14,Fheart rhythm problems, thickening of
OL,15,Fthe heart muscle and heart failure.
OL,17,FHowever, hospital data showed just
OL,18,F2.8% of the group had been diagnosed
OL,19,Fwith cardiac amyloidosis.
