OL,7,FATTR amyloidosis is estimated to
OL,8,Feffect between one in 120,000 and one
OL,9,Fin 830,000 people globally.
OL,11,FNew treatments are being developed at
OL,12,Fthe UCL Centre for Amyloidosis,
OL,13,Fincluding a gene-editing therapy which
OL,14,Fcould stop disease progression.
